<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-12T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="777" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d777">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–1249: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-12T19:00:00-05:00">April 12,
                                1949—7 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>451. Urtel 750 Apr 12 apparently crossed Deptel 447 Apr 11. Dept concurs ur
                        recommendation remain Nanking for reasons outlined Emb reftel.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>